sql:
SELECT team_name, conference, division
FROM teams
WHERE conference = 'Power5';

SELECT teams.team_name, teams.colors, access_logs.access_type
FROM teams
INNER JOIN access_logs ON teams.team_id = access_logs.team_id;

SELECT DISTINCT conference
FROM teams
WHERE division = 'Division I';

external_knowledge:
- "stars in the night sky, shining brighter than ten points per game on average" refers to players scoring more than 10 points per game;
- Teams are the groups of players competing against each other in a sport, typically basketball in this context;
- The count of players refers to how many players in each team meet the criteria of scoring more than ten points per game.

- "Adjusted offense metric" (adj_o) and "adjusted defense metric" (adj_d) refer to the team's performance statistics;
- "Hyperbolic sine" (SINH) of the adjusted defense metric is used to emphasize differences in defensive performance;
- 'SEC' is the Southeastern Conference, a collegiate athletic conference in the United States;
- 'Knee sprain' in the context indicates that an injury of this type occurred during the game, which might have affected game outcomes.

